rows.text: One of the oldest mosques in Afghanistan

Constructed by the Yemeni Merchants and trade settlers of pre Islamic period in pandiya kingdom ordered by Baadhan Governor of Yemen at the time of Muhammad, after they accepted Islam in (628-630)AD. Rebuilt in 11th Century. Its the oldest mosque of India. ibnu Batutah Visited this mosque and said in his travel notes "its the place of where most arab settlers live and he surprised to see them living as in arab land"

Praying hall 5,500 worshipers, outdoor praying area 2,500 worshippers, inaugurated on April 11, 2006, Islamic architectural style prevalent in Bilad Sham, Umayyad-style ornamentation carved in Jordanian stone.

The Great Mosque is the largest and one of the oldest mosques in the Gaza Strip and throughout its history it was Philistine temple, a Byzantine church, an Arab mosque, a Crusader cathedral and was finally transformed back to a mosque by the Mamluks.
The first mosque in Islam history.
